Package com.wingman.defaultplugins.devutils.game

Class Bank

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.wingman.defaultplugins.devutils.game.Bank

  • public class Bank
extends java.lang.Object
    Provides API for getting data about the game bank.
    Most of the functionality only works while the bank interface/widget is opened.

      • getItemIds

        public static java.util.Optional<int[]> getItemIds​()
        Calls ItemContainer.getIds() on the bank's ItemContainer,
        and returns the returned int[].
        Returns:
        an array containing item IDs for item slots, where an "item slot" is an array index; or nothing if the item container couldn't be retrieved

      • getItemQuantities

        public static java.util.Optional<int[]> getItemQuantities​()
        Calls ItemContainer.getQuantities() on the bank's ItemContainer,
        and returns the returned int[].
        Returns:
        an array containing item quantities for item slots, where an "item slot" is an array index; or nothing if the item container couldn't be retrieved

      • getSelectedTab

        public static int getSelectedTab​()
        Returns:
        the currently selected bank tab

      • isOpen

        public static boolean isOpen​()
        Returns:
        true if the bank is open; false otherwise

      • getWidget

        public static java.util.Optional<Widget> getWidget​()
        Returns:
        the bank widget; or nothing if it can't be retrieved (which usually means that the bank isn't open)

      • getWidgets

        public static java.util.Optional<Widget[]> getWidgets​()
        Returns:
        the group of bank related widgets; or nothing if it can't be retrieved (which usually means that the bank isn't open)
